                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=neilsmith",
                        "name": "neilsmith",
                        "displayName": "Neil Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi, I can confirm this patch also resolves the double count issue on Windows where an uploaded path has potential for a shortened alias, such as this (when run as an Apache module as a system service, using system service temp dir) :\r\n\r\nC:\\Windows\\ServiceProfiles\\NetworkService\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\infoschema-query.png\r\nC:\\Windows\\SERVIC~2\\NETWOR~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\infoschema-query.png\r\n\r\nIn this case, it looks like the path is added twice in Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Abstract::isValid()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
